The Station Officer of the State Criminal Investigation Department (SCIID), Panti-Yaba, Mr. Eni Ebri and some officers of the department were yesterday decorated with new ranks. Ebri, popularly called S/O General, was among the newly-promoted officers of the Nigeria Police Force (NPF). He was decorated with the rank of Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) by Mrs. Yetunde Longe, a Deputy Commissioner of Police, who heads the SCIID and Yaba Local Council Development Area (LCDA) Chairman Mr. Kayode Omiyale. Commenting of Ebri’s new rank, one of his friends, Paul Okuweh, described him as a gentleman, who is diligent. He said: “DSP Ebri is one officer that doesn’t joke with his job. His new rank is an evidence of his diligence and reward for hard work.”